            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " and, consequently, to  $X' = X \\cap M$ . So, X' is compatible to Z and M (X' is contained in M) which means that X' is compatible to  $S = Z \\cap M$ . For the same reason,  $X'$  is compatible to  $S'$  and  $Y'$  is compatible to both  $S, S'$ .",
