            "ignore": false,
            "order": 9,
            "anno_id": 1,
            "text": " Recall that  $P = S \\cap S'$  is a 1-dimensional subspace of  $X'$ . Let  $Q$  be the unique 1-dimensional subspace of  $X'$  orthogonal to  $P$ . Since  $X'$  is compatible to  $S$  and  $S'$ , we obtain that  $Q$  is orthogonal to  $S$  and  $S'$ . Therefore,  $Q$  is orthogonal to  $S + S'$  and, consequently, to  $Y' = P<sub>1</sub> + P<sub>2</sub> \\subset S + S'$ .",
            "line_with_spans": [
                {
                    "category_type": "text_span",
                    "poly": [
